      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NEW HOPE (1) collided with another runner last time and always well back when fifth (22.83) in a Grade 6 at this track. Has the ability and looks a key chance. ORANA REX (2) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fourth (16.56) in a Grade 5/6 at this track. Should be about the mark. PUMP FAKE (8) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when seventh at Northam over 297m behind Bodak Yellow (20.45) in a Grade 5/6. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to his name from seven starts. Worth following up. EPIC MARCELINE (4) picked up an unexpected cheque last time and is in the mix again.",
